Moving on to the application segmentation, polyethylene emerges as a major application of olefins, extensively used in packaging materials, containers, pipes, and automotive components. Polypropylene, with its versatility in textiles, plastics, and industrial fibers, continues to drive demand in various end-use industries. Ethylene oxide's application in the production of ethylene glycol for polyester resins highlights the crucial role of olefins in the manufacturing sector. Acrylonitrile and cumene, with their diverse applications across industries, contribute to the overall growth of the olefins market.

